earDisjoint.html#IntermediateField.LinearDisjoint\">LinearDisjoint</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">B</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H'</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">A</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Basic.html#IntermediateField.toSubalgebra\">toSubalgebra</a></span> ⊔ <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">B</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Basic.html#IntermediateField.toSubalgebra\">toSubalgebra</a></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Basis/Defs.html#Module.Basis\">Module.Basis</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">A</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Basis/Defs.html#Module.Basis\">Module.Basis</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">(↥<span class=\"fn\">B</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `A` and `B` are linearly disjoint and such that `A.toSubalgebra ⊔ B.toSubalgebra = ⊤`,\nthen any `F`-basis of `A` is also a `B`-basis of `E`.\nNote that the condition `A.toSubalgebra ⊔ B.toSubalgebra = ⊤` is equivalent to\n`A ⊔ B = ⊤` in many cases, see `IntermediateField.sup_toSubalgebra_of_isAlgebraic_right` and similar\nresults.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/LinearDisjoint.html#IntermediateField.LinearDisjoint.basisOfBasisLeft","kind":"def","line":297,"name":"IntermediateField.L